  "texts": [
    "Alpha (a): waves lie within the range of 8-13 Hz.",
    "In general, the Alpha wave appears as a round or Fig. 34 Ideal skin conductance response (SCR) in the EDA signal [45] sinusoidal-shaped signal and is associated with relaxation and super learning.",
    "Beta (b): Between 14 and 26 Hz, beta waves occur.They're related to things like active thinking, active attention, and problem-solving.",
    "Gamma (c): waves correspond to high values over 30Hz.",
    "These data can be detected and used to detect the presence of specific brain problems.Figure 35 illustrates the four brain waves with their usual amplitude levels."
